  "enhanced_information": "Beta IFN is the drug of choice for relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis (RRMS) as it modulates the immune response and is approved as a first-line treatment due to its efficacy in reducing the frequency of relapses. Natalizumab, although effective in reducing inflammation and relapse rates by blocking immune cell migration to the CNS, is generally reserved for patients with inadequate response to first-line treatments like Beta IFN. Alpha IEN, with its antiviral and antiproliferative properties, is not primarily used for RRMS and is less effective in reducing relapse rates compared to Beta IFN. Gamma IFN is not recommended for RRMS treatment as it can potentially exacerbate autoimmune diseases by increasing the immune response."
